main event: An observer reported seeing an elliptical object with alternating lights in the sky on March 31, 1966, in Long Branch, New Jersey.
interesting points: The object was spinning rapidly and appeared darker than the night sky.,It had four alternating blue-white lights and two additional lights on the bottom.,The observer noted the object's elevation to be around 50 degrees in the western sky.,The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes before the object vanished from view.,The report was sent to Project Blue Book for further investigation but lacked sufficient data.
sighted object: an elliptical object with blue-white lights
witness description: a civilian observing the night sky
